b'Even though every business and every story is different, your experience can be an inspiration to others facing similar struggles. No one makes it on their own. So, throughout Women\xe2\x80\x99s Small Business Month, we\xe2\x80\x99re turning to you to hear about your experiences and listening to your stories. Tell us anything with hashtag #MySBOStory. We\xe2\x80\x99re ready to hear you out. 
 
Here\xe2\x80\x99s what we know: the stakes are high with 62% of women entrepreneurs depending on their business as their primary source of income. So you\xe2\x80\x99re acting swiftly to confront the pandemic, making creative changes at the drop of a dime. Taking businesses outside. Diversifying offerings. Or changing businesses to help neighboring communities. 
 
At the same time, our small business specialists have adapted their expert tools, guidance and resources to guide small business owners through the chaos with grace and creativity. 
 
Now, we want to hear how you\xe2\x80\x99ve made it through the past few months. How are you getting by? What have you learned? How else can we help? Your story deserves to be heard. And we\xe2\x80\x99re listening. Use #MySBOStory to share your ups and downs and in-betweens. #NWSBM'
